      <p>
        Spreadsheets are inherently fragile. A single broken formula or an accidental deletion can lead to catastrophic underbidding. Manual quantity surveying within Excel often lacks the rigorous validation found in dedicated estimation software. Bid accuracy remains the primary differentiator between profitable projects and financial losses. When material prices fluctuate daily, static spreadsheets become obsolete. These tools are no longer sufficient for firms aiming to scale their operations beyond a handful of projects per year.
      </p>
