      <!-- Content on Slow Turnaround and Scaling friction -->
      <p>
        Slow bidding processes act as a friction point in the sales cycle. Prospects perceive a delayed estimate as a sign of organizational inefficiency. Manual cross-referencing of material lists and labor rates consumes valuable time that could be spent on site management or business development. This bottleneck prevents firms from responding to high-value opportunities at the speed required by the market. Profitability is compromised when the time to bid exceeds the window of opportunity.
      </p>
